---
title: "Sequence Diagram: /create-tutorial Skill"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Claude
    participant FS as File System
    participant Grep

    User->>Claude: /create-tutorial <topic> [level]

    alt No topic provided
        Claude->>User: What topic should the tutorial cover?<br/>(skill name / concept / workflow)
        User->>Claude: topic
    end

    note over Claude: Resolve level
    Claude->>Claude: default level = beginner<br/>(beginner / intermediate / reference)

    note over Claude,FS: Check for existing tutorial
    Claude->>FS: Glob docs/tutorial-<slug>.md
    FS-->>Claude: Exists / not found

    alt Tutorial exists
        Claude->>FS: Read existing file
        FS-->>Claude: Previous content + date
        Claude->>User: Update existing or create new version?
        User->>Claude: choice
    end

    note over Claude,Grep: Gather real source material
    Claude->>Grep: Find related SKILL.md / rules / docs<br/>for the topic
    Grep-->>Claude: Paths to read
    Claude->>FS: Read each source
    FS-->>Claude: Real snippets + commands<br/>to quote verbatim

    note over Claude: Compose tutorial
    Claude->>Claude: Apply template:<br/>What & Why → Prerequisites →<br/>Core Concepts (beginner only) →<br/>Steps → Exercise → Verify →<br/>Common Mistakes → Next Steps

    note over Claude: Adapt to audience
    alt level = beginner
        Claude->>Claude: Define every term,<br/>more exposition, 200-400 lines
    else level = intermediate
        Claude->>Claude: Skip intro jargon,<br/>show tradeoffs, 100-200 lines
    else level = reference
        Claude->>Claude: Table-heavy cheatsheet,<br/>no exposition, 50-100 lines
    end

    note over Claude,FS: Save
    Claude->>FS: Write docs/tutorial-<slug>.md
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    note over Claude,FS: Verify
    Claude->>FS: Confirm file exists,<br/>counts lines, checks frontmatter
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    Claude->>User: Summary box with<br/>file path, line count,<br/>level, key sections
